description:
On Misericordia, Damnation A.D. has fully established a truly dominating sound, fueled by sonic dissonance and a much-needed sense of melody. This EP contains five excellent new tracks, including &quot;Bitter&quot; and &quot;Another Day of Darkness.&quot; Yet the highlight is the bonus second half, which features the band at a live radio show playing standout versions of old classics. &quot;No More Dreams&quot; and &quot;On A Pale Horse&quot; are even more punishing than the originals, and the band even throws in a cover of GBH's &quot;Maniac&quot; to close the disc. Misericordia is a must-have for fans of ruthless and earth-shattering distortion, and despite the amateurish production, proves the band has both feet planted firmly in the competitive ground of hardcore metal.
